== Japanese content ==
'''Tawa Shrine''' (たわじんじゃ) is listed in the {{jalink|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932}}, compiled in the Heian period.

It is an {{jalink|Shikinaisha||Engishiki shrine}}, one of the Twenty-Four Shrines of Sanuki. It is traditionally said to be the {{jalink|Sanuki Province|Q929682}} {{jalink|Ichinomiya|Q1656379|Sannomiya}}. Under the {{jalink|modern shrine ranking system|Q712534|former shrine rank}}, it was classified as a {{jalink|Gōsha|Q134917316}}.

Located in {{jalink|Kagawa Prefecture|Q161454}}, {{jalink|Sanuki City|Q857202}}, {{jalink|Shido|Q11490891}} and also in Maeyama, Sanuki City, Kagawa Prefecture, there are two shrines that claim to be the Engishiki-listed shrine, and debate over which one is the true Shikinaisha has continued since the late Edo period without resolution.

Until the end of the Edo period, Ōtao Myōjin in Maeyama Village, Kankawa District (present-day Maeyama, Sanuki City) was worshipped as Tawa Shrine (enshrined deities: Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto and Taokihooi-no-Mikoto), but from around the Meiji period onward, Shido Hachimangū came to be regarded as Tawa Shrine.

=== Tawa Shrine (Shido, Sanuki City) ===
