It adjoins {{ill|lt=Shido-ji Temple|Q11490894|WD=Q11490894}} and was destroyed by fire together with the temple in {{ill|lt=1479|Q6620|WD=Q6620}} ({{ill|lt=Bunmei (Japan)|Q1193544|WD=Q1193544|lt=Bunmei}} 11).

In {{ill|lt=1671|Q7610|WD=Q7610}} ({{ill|lt=Kanbun|Q1146228|WD=Q1146228}} 11), when Shido-ji was restored by {{ill|lt=Takamatsu Domain|Q1036915|WD=Q1036915}} lord {{ill|lt=Matsudaira Yorishige|Q3299364|WD=Q3299364}}, the shrine was also rebuilt. At this time it was relocated to its present site (there is also a theory that it was transferred to the current location in {{ill|lt=1623|Q6818|WD=Q6818}} ({{ill|lt=Genna (Japan)|Q635245|WD=Q635245|lt=Genna}} 9)).

Books and artifacts collected from various regions by Matsuoka Shirabe for research are preserved within the shrine as the “{{ill|lt=Tawa Bunko|Q11430642|WD=Q11430642}} (Kōbokusha)” (Important Cultural Property).

